==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coarctation
<hw>Co`arc*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>coarctatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Confinement to a narrow
space.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pressure; that which presses.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A stricture or narrowing, as of a
canal, cavity, or orifice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coarse</ent>⟦br⟧
